<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!--
	═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
	RELEASE (Matt / Sparkle) entitlements — 2026-06-14 CloudKit env split.

	WHY A SEPARATE FILE: Voxhora-Mac.entitlements is consumed by BOTH
	deploy.sh (Patrick's Debug) AND, previously, release.sh's final codesign.
	Adding the Production CloudKit key to that shared file would also flip
	Patrick's Debug Mac to Production (a Debug build honors the key when it's
	set), hiding his Development data — a HARD-RULE violation. So the Release
	pipeline now seals against THIS file instead:
	  • release.sh  → --entitlements Voxhora-Mac/Voxhora-Mac-Release.entitlements
	  • project.yml → Release config CODE_SIGN_ENTITLEMENTS points here
	Debug (deploy.sh) keeps using Voxhora-Mac.entitlements (no env key →
	Development), so Patrick stays on Development no matter what.

	CURRENT STATE: identical to Voxhora-Mac.entitlements (still Development —
	NO icloud-container-environment key). The product has NOT been flipped to
	Production yet; per the HARD RULE, Matt's Development data must be exported
	and verified in Production BEFORE the flip.

	TO FLIP TO PRODUCTION (Step 3 of the migration, Release build only):
	uncomment the two lines marked ⟵ FLIP below, then run release.sh. The
	embedded Dev-ID Direct profile already authorizes the Production value
	(verified 2026-06-14 — see voxhora_cloudkit_prod_migration_tool memory).
	═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
	-->

	<!-- ⟵ FLIP: uncomment to move the RELEASE build to the Production CloudKit DB
	<key>com.apple.developer.icloud-container-environment</key>
	<string>Production</string>
	-->

	<key>com.apple.application-identifier</key>
	<string>S4GM27H6N5.com.patrickfagerberg.voxhora.mac</string>
	<key>com.apple.developer.team-identifier</key>
	<string>S4GM27H6N5</string>
	<key>com.apple.developer.icloud-container-identifiers</key>
	<array>
		<string>iCloud.com.patrickfagerberg.voxhora</string>
	</array>
	<key>com.apple.developer.icloud-services</key>
	<array>
		<string>CloudKit</string>
		<string>CloudDocuments</string>
	</array>
	<key>com.apple.developer.ubiquity-container-identifiers</key>
	<array>
		<string>iCloud.com.patrickfagerberg.voxhora</string>
	</array>
	<key>com.apple.developer.aps-environment</key>
	<string>production</string>
	<key>com.apple.security.application-groups</key>
	<array>
		<string>group.com.patrickfagerberg.voxhora</string>
	</array>
	<key>keychain-access-groups</key>
	<array>
		<string>S4GM27H6N5.com.patrickfagerberg.voxhora.shared</string>
	</array>
	<key>com.apple.security.automation.apple-events</key>
	<true/>
	<key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
	<true/>
	<key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
	<true/>
</dict>
</plist>
